I don’t recall if they still have a Bixby button on the newer Samsung phones, but I use an app called bxActions to set mine to play/pause media with a double tap (single tap resulted in accidental presses in my pocket). It’s nice, because I don’t have to wake up the phone to play/pause when I don’t have a bluetooth device to control it with.

The downside is that it requires enabling developer mode and doing some light fiddling with dev/debug tools to enable double press actions with bxActions.

snippet.textDisplay:
Here's what i do for my phone set up.
I have the Xiaomi MI A3 which is an Android One phone. It has SD card support. So i take advantage of that. I keep all of my, word docs, photos, videos, wallpapers, ringtones and mp3s on the sd card. That way i can easily transfer those files between devices if I need to. And i don't have to worry about losing those files if the phone breaks as long as the sd card is intact.,


I also use dark mode with a touch of Hello Kitty. lol I Like to be very C*A*P. Cute And Practical! I use the system wide dark mode on any apps that support it and dark colored Hello Kitty wallpapers for my lock and home screen.
